ceph-menv

Installation

1. Build links
# UMSTOR_OS_PATH is the host directory of your UMStor-OS project, e.g. /data/UMStor-OS/
$ cd ceph-menv
$ sh ./build_links.sh $UMSTOR_OS_PATH


2. Add alias

To your shell startup script (such as $HOME/.bashrc) add:

e.g.

alias mset='source ~/ceph-menv/mset.sh'


3. Modify PATH

Add path to ceph-menv/bin to PATH. It should precede any reference to your UMStor-OS project binary path (e.g. /data/UMStor-OS/build/bin/).


4. Modify PS1:

Add references to $MRUN_PROMPT and potentially $MRUN_PROMPT_COLOR in PS1 in $HOME/.bashrc, for example:

case "$TERM" in
xterm-*color)
    PS1='${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}\[\033[$MRUN_PROMPT_COLOR;1m\]${MRUN_PROMPT}\[\033[01;32m\]\u@\h\[\033[00m\]:\[\033[01;34m\]\w\[\033[00m\]\$ '
    ;;
*)
    PS1='${debian_chroot:+($debian_chroot)}${MRUN_PROMPT}\u@\h:\w\$ '
    ;;
esac
